1
00:00:33,742 --> 00:00:36,286
-How old are you?
-Seven.

2
00:00:36,453 --> 00:00:39,289
I'm seven too, and so is he.

3
00:00:40,790 --> 00:00:42,917
My name is Sung Duk-mi,

4
00:00:43,042 --> 00:00:44,836
and his name is Nam Eun-gi.

5
00:00:45,086 --> 00:00:46,629
What is your name?

6
00:00:47,005 --> 00:00:48,173
My name is

7
00:00:49,841 --> 00:00:50,967
Heo Yun-jae.

8
00:00:51,134 --> 00:00:52,469
Are you waiting for your mom?

9
00:00:54,262 --> 00:00:55,597
Do you want to play with us?

10
00:01:54,239 --> 00:01:55,615
Did you sleep well?

11
00:01:57,325 --> 00:01:58,535
What about you?

12
00:02:00,411 --> 00:02:01,663
Are you still sleepy?

13
00:02:01,746 --> 00:02:03,957
It's still bedtime.

14
00:02:04,415 --> 00:02:05,792
It's your birthday today.

15
00:02:12,340 --> 00:02:13,591
Happy birthday.

16
00:02:13,758 --> 00:02:15,009
Thank you.

17
00:02:16,678 --> 00:02:18,304
You're not even opening your eyes.

18
00:02:20,014 --> 00:02:21,474
Don't you want to see me?

19
00:02:26,688 --> 00:02:30,859
Wow, I get to see your face
as soon as I wake up.

20
00:02:31,818 --> 00:02:33,778
This is an amazing birthday.

21
00:02:36,781 --> 00:02:38,116
You need to get up now.

22
00:02:42,203 --> 00:02:43,705
It's my birthday.

23
00:02:43,788 --> 00:02:45,206
I don't need to get up.

24
00:02:47,417 --> 00:02:48,877
Okay, then. Sleep a bit more.

25
00:02:49,502 --> 00:02:51,838
Should we just stay like this
instead of going to work?

26
00:02:51,921 --> 00:02:53,631
How about we both quit

27
00:02:54,257 --> 00:02:55,341
and become jobless?

28
00:02:58,177 --> 00:03:00,346
-I'll get up.
-I'm serious.

29
00:03:02,056 --> 00:03:04,642
Let's stay in bed like this all day
and not go to work.

30
00:03:06,978 --> 00:03:08,229
-Can't we do that?
-No, we can't.

31
00:03:08,313 --> 00:03:09,355
Why not?

32
00:03:12,775 --> 00:03:14,068
You're too precious.

33
00:03:15,028 --> 00:03:16,404
You're too precious to look at all day.

34
00:03:19,157 --> 00:03:20,408
Duk-mi.

35
00:03:22,285 --> 00:03:24,662
Duk-mi, you are darn--

36
00:03:24,746 --> 00:03:26,706
Darn pretty even in the morning.

37
00:03:32,003 --> 00:03:33,087
You're dirty.

38
00:03:39,969 --> 00:03:41,387
How can you say I'm dirty?

39
00:03:52,607 --> 00:03:53,983
Don't be scared.

40
00:03:54,525 --> 00:03:56,069
Will I be able to go to work?

41
00:03:56,194 --> 00:03:57,946
-Here we go.
-Oh, no.

42
00:03:58,029 --> 00:04:00,073
-Why are you shaking?
-I'm not shaking.

43
00:04:00,156 --> 00:04:01,324
Do you not trust me?

44
00:04:03,076 --> 00:04:04,452
What's all this?

45
00:04:05,245 --> 00:04:07,205
It's your birthday,
so you should eat seaweed soup.

46
00:04:07,288 --> 00:04:08,915
Are you going to cook it yourself?

47
00:04:08,998 --> 00:04:09,916
Yes.

48
00:04:12,418 --> 00:04:15,004
But what are these Cheongyang chili
and ginseng for?

49
00:04:15,088 --> 00:04:17,423
You love Cheongyang chili,

50
00:04:17,590 --> 00:04:19,592
and ginseng is good for your body.

51
00:04:20,677 --> 00:04:23,763
But I don't think you're supposed
to add them in seaweed soup.

52
00:04:24,013 --> 00:04:27,350
Really? Then I'll use them
to make gimbap later.

53
00:04:27,892 --> 00:04:28,768
Okay.

54
00:04:30,937 --> 00:04:32,772
I can't wait to eat ginseng gimbap.

55
00:04:39,737 --> 00:04:40,822
Is this enough?

56
00:04:42,156 --> 00:04:45,034
Director Gold,
this whole thing is for 60 servings.

57
00:04:45,285 --> 00:04:47,870
So this much will be enough
to feed 20 people.

58
00:04:50,081 --> 00:04:53,126
Then should I take out this much?

59
00:04:54,210 --> 00:04:56,254
I'll cook a delicious meal for you.
Just wait a little bit.

60
00:04:56,337 --> 00:04:58,464
Okay, I'm counting on you.

61
00:05:03,136 --> 00:05:05,221
-This one?
-Yes, it looks nice.

62
00:05:05,346 --> 00:05:07,515
You also need to get changed.

63
00:05:07,598 --> 00:05:08,808
I'm just going to wear this.

64
00:05:08,891 --> 00:05:12,270
Don't you think our colleagues know
a bit too much about us?

65
00:05:12,353 --> 00:05:14,522
Are you embarrassed, Mr. Shy Boy?

66
00:05:14,605 --> 00:05:16,983
Then just wear my clothes to work.
I'll pick out an outfit for you.

67
00:05:19,652 --> 00:05:22,655
Gosh, fine. I'll just go home
and get changed.

68
00:05:24,198 --> 00:05:25,658
I think this will look nice on you.

69
00:05:25,950 --> 00:05:26,868
What?

70
00:05:32,123 --> 00:05:33,249
What are you doing?

71
00:05:36,169 --> 00:05:37,253
Let me apply it for you.

72
00:05:37,336 --> 00:05:38,838
Have you done it before?

73
00:05:39,130 --> 00:05:40,465
I'm Ryan Gold.

74
00:05:52,518 --> 00:05:53,770
You look pretty.

75
00:05:55,688 --> 00:05:58,024
Now, it's my turn to put lipstick on you.

76
00:06:10,578 --> 00:06:12,330
I think you need a bit more.

77
00:06:29,514 --> 00:06:31,099
Is this how you want me to go to work?

78
00:06:32,725 --> 00:06:33,768
It's pretty.

79
00:06:34,102 --> 00:06:35,853
You look a lot more lively.

80
00:06:40,942 --> 00:06:43,945
Can I be a movie star
since it's my birthday today?

81
00:06:51,119 --> 00:06:52,495
Don't I look like a celebrity?

82
00:06:56,499 --> 00:06:57,708
You already fell for me

83
00:07:02,505 --> 00:07:04,799
I caught your eyes

84
00:07:04,882 --> 00:07:06,259
I make your heart ache

85
00:07:09,387 --> 00:07:12,390
I sweep everyone off their feet

86
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:18,271
A runway spreads out
A highway opens for me

87
00:07:23,693 --> 00:07:26,821
You'll never be able to forget my name

88
00:07:32,118 --> 00:07:33,703
Seung-min, drink this.

89
00:07:33,995 --> 00:07:35,830
Thank you, Seon-ju.

90
00:07:36,873 --> 00:07:38,916
Are you working?
Is it a variety show proposal?

91
00:07:39,125 --> 00:07:40,126
No.

92
00:07:40,543 --> 00:07:44,172
Remember how I said I'm only going
to focus on making you laugh?

93
00:07:44,255 --> 00:07:46,132
So I thought about
what we should do together

94
00:07:46,215 --> 00:07:48,259
and wrote a proposal on that.

95
00:07:48,342 --> 00:07:49,802
You even wrote a proposal?

96
00:07:50,011 --> 00:07:52,138
Listen. This is the title.

97
00:07:52,221 --> 00:07:53,973
Will It Work on a Campsite?

98
00:07:54,223 --> 00:07:55,683
-Camping?
-Yes.

99
00:07:56,184 --> 00:07:59,937
It's about us going camping
every weekend with Geon-u.

100
00:08:00,354 --> 00:08:02,982
We can cook outside and look
at the stars in the night sky.

101
00:08:03,065 --> 00:08:04,442
We'll be able to relax and recharge.

102
00:08:05,485 --> 00:08:07,653
But do we even have a tent?

103
00:08:07,737 --> 00:08:10,156
We need to buy one. There are a lot
of camping tools we need to buy.

104
00:08:10,239 --> 00:08:12,533
Portable pots and pans,
a burner, a lantern, and...

105
00:08:12,617 --> 00:08:15,161
Seung-min, as you already know,

106
00:08:15,578 --> 00:08:16,954
I'm very sensitive about where I sleep.

107
00:08:17,038 --> 00:08:18,915
Oh, I forgot about that. Then...

108
00:08:21,125 --> 00:08:22,877
Then should we just buy a camping car?

109
00:08:26,923 --> 00:08:28,925
-Is there anything else?
-Of course.

110
00:08:29,342 --> 00:08:31,260
Here's the title of my second proposal.

111
00:08:32,011 --> 00:08:33,262
Fishing over Flowers.

112
00:08:33,346 --> 00:08:35,056
-Fishing?
-Yes.

113
00:08:35,223 --> 00:08:37,266
I heard night fishing is really great.

114
00:08:37,350 --> 00:08:40,895
It's more about
spending time together than fishing.

115
00:08:41,020 --> 00:08:43,022
We can have long conversations.
And once it gets dark,

116
00:08:43,105 --> 00:08:45,191
-we can sleep in a tent while...
-The tent, again?

117
00:08:45,274 --> 00:08:47,109
Oh, right. If you don't want
to sleep in a tent...

118
00:08:47,818 --> 00:08:49,153
We should get a camping car after all.

119
00:08:51,572 --> 00:08:53,115
-Seung-min.
-Yes?

120
00:08:53,282 --> 00:08:56,118
Instead of trying to do things I'd like,

121
00:08:56,285 --> 00:08:58,204
how about you focus more

122
00:08:58,287 --> 00:09:00,206
on trying not to do things
that I don't like?

123
00:09:00,289 --> 00:09:02,458
-Not doing things you don't like?
-Yes.

124
00:09:03,834 --> 00:09:04,877
I understand.

125
00:09:05,628 --> 00:09:07,964
Then, in order to learn
about the things you don't like,

126
00:09:08,130 --> 00:09:09,715
we need to talk to each other a lot.

127
00:09:09,924 --> 00:09:12,843
-So fishing is--
-That's enough. Stop it!

128
00:09:13,010 --> 00:09:14,679
My gosh, okay.

129
00:09:14,971 --> 00:09:16,305
I should go to work now.

130
00:09:17,139 --> 00:09:18,599
Let's talk a lot in the evening

131
00:09:18,849 --> 00:09:20,226
about the things you don't like

132
00:09:20,935 --> 00:09:23,145
-while we fish.
-Hey, just get lost.

133
00:09:24,689 --> 00:09:26,107
What's wrong with him?

134
00:09:27,024 --> 00:09:28,776
If that dumfounded laugh
also counts as a laugh,

135
00:09:29,235 --> 00:09:30,695
your husband succeeded.

136
00:09:33,531 --> 00:09:36,075
Isn't Seung-min so cute?

137
00:09:37,285 --> 00:09:39,537
This is the final design
of the exhibition space.

138
00:09:39,620 --> 00:09:41,330
Did you run a simulation
of the exhibition route?

139
00:09:41,414 --> 00:09:44,584
Yes, Mr. Cha's exhibition room is expected
to be the most crowded,

140
00:09:44,667 --> 00:09:47,211
so we assigned him
to the most spacious area.

141
00:09:47,295 --> 00:09:49,672
The temporary walls
will start getting built next week,

142
00:09:49,755 --> 00:09:52,592
and they're going to get painted
as soon as they get installed.

143
00:09:52,675 --> 00:09:54,385
How about we use a stronger color

144
00:09:54,635 --> 00:09:56,721
for the main wall at the entrance
of the exhibition hall?

145
00:09:57,138 --> 00:09:58,180
Got it.

146
00:10:00,141 --> 00:10:01,684
Did you hire all the staff?

147
00:10:01,767 --> 00:10:04,854
We finished hiring the docent
and the guards.

148
00:10:04,937 --> 00:10:07,106
And they'll be receiving training
starting from next week.

149
00:10:07,815 --> 00:10:10,234
Okay, then I guess everything's--

150
00:10:10,318 --> 00:10:13,904
Director Gold, you need to prepare
an opening speech.

151
00:10:14,947 --> 00:10:15,906
Okay.

152
00:10:19,201 --> 00:10:20,661
-Duk-mi.
-Yes?

153
00:10:22,997 --> 00:10:23,914
I know we're busy, but

154
00:10:23,998 --> 00:10:25,958
it's our first time
celebrating your birthday together.

155
00:10:26,042 --> 00:10:27,501
You'll make time for me tonight, right?

156
00:10:27,585 --> 00:10:29,295
I guess I can do that for you.

157
00:10:29,378 --> 00:10:32,381
Our goal today is to get off work on time.

158
00:10:46,854 --> 00:10:49,482
Your mom told you to wait
in the playground?

159
00:10:51,651 --> 00:10:53,277
She told me that she'll be back soon.

160
00:10:55,988 --> 00:10:57,323
What's your name?

161
00:10:57,698 --> 00:10:58,741
Yun-jae.

162
00:10:59,825 --> 00:11:00,910
Heo Yun-jae.

163
00:11:01,118 --> 00:11:03,746
You must be hungry, Yun-jae.

164
00:11:04,038 --> 00:11:06,123
Would you like to come
to my house and have some food?

165
00:11:08,709 --> 00:11:12,004
Why not? Duk-mi and Eun-gi
are also going to eat together.

166
00:11:12,088 --> 00:11:15,049
I need to wait for my mom

167
00:11:15,424 --> 00:11:16,550
in the playground.

168
00:11:18,886 --> 00:11:22,223
Then I'll wait there instead.

169
00:11:22,306 --> 00:11:25,559
I'll let you know when your mom comes.
What do you say?

170
00:11:28,020 --> 00:11:30,356
Now, go on upstairs and eat.

171
00:11:30,564 --> 00:11:31,816
Wash your hands first.

172
00:11:31,899 --> 00:11:33,150
-Okay!
-Okay!

173
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:45,996
Why do you keep looking at this?

174
00:11:47,164 --> 00:11:49,542
Why do you think Eun-gi asked us

175
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:51,293
that boy's name yesterday?

176
00:11:52,545 --> 00:11:54,255
He said he just asked for no reason.

177
00:11:54,964 --> 00:11:56,173
Eun-gi has

178
00:11:57,508 --> 00:12:01,971
never once talked about that day
even by mistake.

179
00:12:03,764 --> 00:12:06,267
I've always felt bad but grateful for it.

180
00:12:10,521 --> 00:12:12,273
I think something's up.

181
00:12:12,773 --> 00:12:14,442
Something he can't tell me about.

182
00:12:16,861 --> 00:12:18,320
If it's something he can't say,

183
00:12:19,071 --> 00:12:20,448
then he won't say it.

184
00:12:20,573 --> 00:12:22,783
If it's something that he should,
then he'll tell us.

185
00:12:23,242 --> 00:12:24,535
Be patient with him.

186
00:12:34,420 --> 00:12:35,921
Would you like to head in first?

187
00:12:36,422 --> 00:12:37,840
Why? We can go in together.

188
00:12:38,424 --> 00:12:40,259
I'm worried that we're slightly late.

189
00:12:41,177 --> 00:12:42,094
Sure thing.

190
00:12:53,647 --> 00:12:55,649
Hello, did you make a reservation?

191
00:12:55,733 --> 00:12:57,359
Yes, it's under Ryan Gold.

192
00:13:01,822 --> 00:13:04,450
Happy birthday to you

193
00:13:04,825 --> 00:13:07,369
Happy birthday to you

194
00:13:08,245 --> 00:13:09,580
Happy birthday, Ms. Sung.

195
00:13:15,711 --> 00:13:16,837
Mr. Cha.

196
00:13:21,592 --> 00:13:23,260
You should make a wish.

197
00:13:27,014 --> 00:13:29,058
There's nothing to wish for anymore.

198
00:13:31,685 --> 00:13:33,062
My brother's great and all,

199
00:13:33,270 --> 00:13:35,648
but I can't believe he's late
to the party he prepared himself.

200
00:13:35,731 --> 00:13:36,982
I hope you forgive him.

201
00:13:37,983 --> 00:13:39,652
Director Gold is running late?

202
00:13:39,735 --> 00:13:43,322
Yes, that's why he told me
to wish you a happy birthday first.

203
00:13:43,781 --> 00:13:45,616
That's why I came running.

204
00:13:48,536 --> 00:13:51,372
I'm fine with us meeting
Director Gold and Ms. Sung,

205
00:13:51,664 --> 00:13:53,958
but won't we be ruining their date?

206
00:13:54,041 --> 00:13:56,669
Are you seriously still calling him that?

207
00:13:56,835 --> 00:13:57,795
He's Yun-jae.

208
00:13:58,003 --> 00:13:59,046
Heo Yun-jae.

209
00:13:59,713 --> 00:14:02,466
Also, what's so bad
about crashing their date? We can do that.

210
00:14:03,217 --> 00:14:04,260
Okay.

211
00:14:08,639 --> 00:14:10,015
Here's your mission.

212
00:14:10,266 --> 00:14:12,810
You, and only you,

213
00:14:13,269 --> 00:14:15,938
will go into the next room
and wish Duk-mi a happy birthday.

214
00:14:16,021 --> 00:14:17,273
I'm running a bit late, you see.

215
00:14:18,566 --> 00:14:19,608
Who is that?

216
00:14:19,900 --> 00:14:21,402
It's Ryan.

217
00:14:22,194 --> 00:14:24,154
Mom, wait here for a second.

218
00:14:26,991 --> 00:14:28,784
-Is that so?
-Yes.

219
00:14:28,951 --> 00:14:30,870
I didn't even know
that it was your birthday.

220
00:14:30,953 --> 00:14:33,080
If I had known, I would've bought a gift.

221
00:14:33,622 --> 00:14:34,915
My Si-an,

222
00:14:35,499 --> 00:14:37,042
you are my gift.

223
00:14:39,336 --> 00:14:40,629
Just a second.

224
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:46,969
How do you like my gift to you?

225
00:14:48,971 --> 00:14:50,890
-Is that Ryan?
-Yes.

226
00:14:52,725 --> 00:14:56,020
I'm the most ecstatic fangirl
in this entire world now.

227
00:14:56,103 --> 00:14:57,187
Thank you.

228
00:15:02,443 --> 00:15:04,194
You have 20 minutes.

229
00:15:04,278 --> 00:15:08,157
Just make sure you don't enjoy his company
more than you enjoy mine.

230
00:15:12,870 --> 00:15:15,998
We're ruining Ms. Sung's birthday.
You should've spent it with her alone.

231
00:15:16,081 --> 00:15:17,041
It's all right.

232
00:15:17,499 --> 00:15:18,959
I'm sure she'll love it too.

233
00:15:20,002 --> 00:15:23,422
In 20 minutes,
we'll go and join the party.

234
00:15:23,672 --> 00:15:24,590
In 20 minutes?

235
00:15:27,801 --> 00:15:28,886
I like it,

236
00:15:29,929 --> 00:15:32,932
being alone with my mother.

237
00:15:35,267 --> 00:15:36,226
Thank you

238
00:15:36,936 --> 00:15:38,395
for calling me your mother.

239
00:15:40,898 --> 00:15:41,774
Actually,

240
00:15:42,566 --> 00:15:44,068
it's still a bit awkward.

241
00:15:44,735 --> 00:15:48,197
I promise to say it more comfortably
over time.

242
00:15:48,739 --> 00:15:51,200
I know it's awkward for you too,

243
00:15:53,035 --> 00:15:54,495
but please call me casually.

244
00:15:57,831 --> 00:15:58,916
Yun-jae.

245
00:16:00,250 --> 00:16:01,543
Yes, Mother.

246
00:16:06,590 --> 00:16:09,802
It's Ms. Sung's birthday,
but I'm receiving the gift.

247
00:16:12,596 --> 00:16:14,306
It's September 12.

248
00:16:16,225 --> 00:16:17,643
Yun-jae, your birthday is

249
00:16:18,769 --> 00:16:20,187
September 12.

250
00:16:22,564 --> 00:16:23,941
September 12.

251
00:16:27,695 --> 00:16:29,780
We should celebrate it together this year.

252
00:16:32,908 --> 00:16:35,285
That reminds me. I brought photos.

253
00:16:35,869 --> 00:16:37,538
There aren't many though.

254
00:16:44,586 --> 00:16:48,382
I've lived my life remembering you
at this age.

255
00:16:49,216 --> 00:16:52,302
"How tall would he be at ten?

256
00:16:53,137 --> 00:16:55,764
What would he be like at 20?"

257
00:16:56,306 --> 00:16:57,975
You have no idea

258
00:16:59,351 --> 00:17:00,686
how much I missed you.

259
00:17:12,865 --> 00:17:14,199
I'll show you

260
00:17:15,034 --> 00:17:18,328
how I looked at ten, and twenty too.

261
00:17:21,415 --> 00:17:22,958
I have many photos.

262
00:17:23,292 --> 00:17:24,251
