00:41:35,117 --> 00:41:36,202
I lacked

539
00:41:37,244 --> 00:41:38,829
as a father,

540
00:41:44,084 --> 00:41:45,294
and your mom was left

541
00:41:46,045 --> 00:41:48,797
to pick up all the burden for too long.

542
00:41:52,301 --> 00:41:55,387
If I had been a more competent husband,

543
00:41:56,180 --> 00:41:59,350
she wouldn't have had
to abandon Yun-jae like that.

544
00:42:04,939 --> 00:42:06,690
Your mother really had no choice.

545
00:42:08,234 --> 00:42:09,360
It was me

546
00:42:11,862 --> 00:42:14,615
who made her make such a cruel decision.

547
00:42:26,669 --> 00:42:27,670
Duk-mi,

548
00:42:29,838 --> 00:42:32,967
I'm ashamed to even say this to you,

549
00:42:34,718 --> 00:42:37,221
but since you're now all grown up,

550
00:42:39,056 --> 00:42:40,057
I think

551
00:42:41,267 --> 00:42:42,268
we can

552
00:42:42,351 --> 00:42:44,270
finally let your mother be at ease.

553
00:42:48,023 --> 00:42:50,150
Would that be all right, Duk-mi?

554
00:43:36,905 --> 00:43:38,198
Duk-mi!

555
00:43:52,713 --> 00:43:56,258
-Duk-mi, hurry!
-Why?

556
00:43:57,885 --> 00:43:59,178
Over there!

557
00:44:00,596 --> 00:44:02,222
Do you want to ride one, Duk-su?

558
00:44:02,431 --> 00:44:05,476
Yes, Giddy-up, horsey!

559
00:44:08,687 --> 00:44:10,731
All right. I'll buy you a turn.

560
00:44:10,814 --> 00:44:13,067
Nice!

561
00:44:18,280 --> 00:44:20,783
DALNIM KINDERGARTEN

562
00:44:27,831 --> 00:44:29,166
Duk-mi!

563
00:44:29,416 --> 00:44:30,709
Duk-su!

564
00:44:35,964 --> 00:44:37,800
Duk-su.

565
00:44:43,472 --> 00:44:44,723
Mom.

566
00:44:47,184 --> 00:44:49,603
Duk-su's hand is so cold.

567
00:45:06,537 --> 00:45:07,871
Duk-su.

568
00:45:23,095 --> 00:45:24,346
Please give her some time.

569
00:45:24,847 --> 00:45:26,849
Give my mom some time to tell Duk-mi.

570
00:45:28,767 --> 00:45:31,687
Also, Duk-mi will need time
to absorb everything.

571
00:45:33,522 --> 00:45:34,773
Duk-mi.

572
00:45:36,650 --> 00:45:39,820
She's tough,
so I'm sure she'll be all right.

573
00:45:46,910 --> 00:45:48,162
Duk-mi.

574
00:45:50,831 --> 00:45:52,875
Mom, I'm sorry.

575
00:45:54,001 --> 00:45:55,919
I'm so sorry.

576
00:45:58,005 --> 00:45:59,006
Don't cry.

577
00:46:00,757 --> 00:46:01,925
Don't you cry.

578
00:46:18,984 --> 00:46:22,029
Mom, I'm sorry for erasing the memories

579
00:46:22,905 --> 00:46:24,615
and making it harder for you.

580
00:46:24,823 --> 00:46:26,241
I was able

581
00:46:27,826 --> 00:46:30,162
to keep it together thanks to you.

582
00:46:34,666 --> 00:46:36,126
Because

583
00:46:36,335 --> 00:46:38,170
you forgot about it all and stayed happy

584
00:46:38,921 --> 00:46:41,215
and because you grew up in the light,

585
00:46:42,049 --> 00:46:45,511
I was able to endure the pain as well.

586
00:46:48,430 --> 00:46:49,681
Still, I'm sorry.

587
00:46:51,099 --> 00:46:54,061
Everyone had to live
with a painful memory,

588
00:46:54,937 --> 00:46:56,897
but only I erased it from my mind.

589
00:46:57,981 --> 00:46:59,775
I'm sorry for being a coward.

590
00:47:03,362 --> 00:47:05,113
At the scene of the accident,

591
00:47:06,615 --> 00:47:09,493
I was told that you wouldn't let go

592
00:47:09,576 --> 00:47:11,286
of Duk-su's hand.

593
00:47:13,413 --> 00:47:15,457
That's why I'm sure

594
00:47:15,541 --> 00:47:17,960
he didn't feel alone
during his last moments.

595
00:47:18,877 --> 00:47:20,212
I know very well

596
00:47:21,046 --> 00:47:24,132
how much you adored
and loved your little brother.

597
00:47:25,759 --> 00:47:29,096
So it's all right.
Everything's all right now.

598
00:47:30,931 --> 00:47:31,932
I remember

599
00:47:32,724 --> 00:47:33,892
everything now.

600
00:47:35,435 --> 00:47:37,938
I remember both Director Gold and Duk-su.

601
00:47:39,731 --> 00:47:40,899
Let's not

602
00:47:41,608 --> 00:47:44,945
hold back what we want to say anymore.

603
00:47:46,446 --> 00:47:47,906
We'll talk about Duk-su

604
00:47:49,157 --> 00:47:51,201
and cherish and remember his life.

605
00:47:54,454 --> 00:47:55,998
Thank you, my daughter.

606
00:47:58,542 --> 00:47:59,710
Thank you.

607
00:48:09,720 --> 00:48:11,179
Also

608
00:48:11,597 --> 00:48:12,681
Duk-mi,

609
00:48:14,224 --> 00:48:15,517
Eun-gi...

610
00:48:17,769 --> 00:48:20,397
Eun-gi was young back then too,

611
00:48:20,647 --> 00:48:23,942
but he had to live through Duk-su's death

612
00:48:24,610 --> 00:48:26,820
and you suffering from memory loss.

613
00:48:26,903 --> 00:48:29,156
He had to be strong for all our sake.

614
00:48:29,865 --> 00:48:33,619
Though he never said anything,
I'm sure it took a toll on him too.

615
00:48:45,589 --> 00:48:46,673
Eun-gi.

616
00:48:49,009 --> 00:48:49,926
Thank you

617
00:48:50,636 --> 00:48:54,681
for being there for my parents
and comforting them through the pain.

618
00:49:01,980 --> 00:49:03,273
Come to think of it,

619
00:49:05,025 --> 00:49:08,362
you were the one who always had my back,

620
00:49:09,738 --> 00:49:11,823
and I took it for granted.

621
00:49:13,659 --> 00:49:14,910
You are, after all,

622
00:49:17,329 --> 00:49:18,747
my idiotic Eun-gi.

623
00:49:19,289 --> 00:49:22,042
That was me being your fanboy.

624
00:49:26,672 --> 00:49:28,215
-Duk-mi.
-Yes?

625
00:49:29,132 --> 00:49:30,384
Are you all right?

626
00:49:30,926 --> 00:49:32,928
No, I'm not.

627
00:49:36,431 --> 00:49:39,142
How did you cope with it all
at that young age?

628
00:49:41,269 --> 00:49:44,231
I could because we're family.

629
00:49:55,492 --> 00:49:57,285
I'm also grateful

630
00:49:58,412 --> 00:49:59,913
to the seven-year-old Eun-gi as well.

631
00:50:00,706 --> 00:50:04,668
The same goes to the 33-year-old Eun-gi

632
00:50:05,293 --> 00:50:06,753
who's here with me now.

633
00:50:07,838 --> 00:50:08,839
I'm sorry too.

634
00:50:10,841 --> 00:50:14,428
Duk-mi, I guess I only told you
that your smile looks pretty

635
00:50:14,511 --> 00:50:16,096
and not the other thing.

636
00:50:17,472 --> 00:50:19,766
You're really ugly when you cry.

637
00:50:21,810 --> 00:50:23,019
You liar.

638
00:50:23,770 --> 00:50:24,980
It's not a lie.

639
00:50:29,025 --> 00:50:30,485
You're going to tell

640
00:50:31,903 --> 00:50:33,071
Director Gold, right?

641
00:50:36,074 --> 00:50:37,325
Then I wish you the best.

642
00:50:47,544 --> 00:50:49,296
-Good morning, Director Gold.
-Good morning.

643
00:50:52,424 --> 00:50:55,093
Oh, I guess Ms. Sung
is running a bit late today.

644
00:50:55,802 --> 00:50:57,095
Please give her some time.

645
00:50:57,471 --> 00:50:59,347
Give my mom some time to tell Duk-mi.

646
00:50:59,598 --> 00:51:01,600
Also, Duk-mi will need time
to absorb everything.

647
00:51:02,350 --> 00:51:05,520
-Let Ms. Sung take today off.
-Good morning.

648
00:51:09,900 --> 00:51:11,234
I'm here, Director Gold.

649
00:51:12,110 --> 00:51:13,111
Duk-mi.

650
00:51:13,653 --> 00:51:15,322
I have something to tell you.

651
00:51:30,504 --> 00:51:31,838
-Duk-mi.
-Director Gold.

652
00:51:36,384 --> 00:51:37,803
Eun-gi told me

653
00:51:39,262 --> 00:51:40,764
that you regained your memory.

654
00:51:45,435 --> 00:51:48,647
It was too hard to bear,
and I didn't know what to do.

655
00:51:49,356 --> 00:51:51,942
-I just wanted to hide.
-Don't do that.

656
00:51:53,109 --> 00:51:55,320
If you do that,
it'll be too hard for me to handle.

657
00:51:58,365 --> 00:52:00,116
But I thought it'd be too hard for you,

658
00:52:00,492 --> 00:52:03,829
so I decided to see you
with a smile on my face.

659
00:52:06,373 --> 00:52:07,874
I thought if we share the pain,

660
00:52:08,750 --> 00:52:10,502
it would be a little better.

661
00:52:13,046 --> 00:52:14,214
Thank you.

662
00:52:15,382 --> 00:52:16,424
My mom...

663
00:52:18,718 --> 00:52:20,720
My mom is here.

664
00:52:21,346 --> 00:52:24,766
She wants to see you in person
and apologize.

665
00:52:27,978 --> 00:52:29,938
My mom...

666
00:52:30,522 --> 00:52:32,065
It's okay, Duk-mi.

667
00:52:32,482 --> 00:52:33,483
It's okay.

668
00:52:50,792 --> 00:52:51,960
I'll be back.

669
00:52:53,587 --> 00:52:54,796
Wait for me.

670
00:53:27,954 --> 00:53:30,123
Duk-mi told me everything.

671
00:53:30,457 --> 00:53:31,499
That your mother

672
00:53:32,334 --> 00:53:34,669
couldn't come because of an accident.

673
00:53:35,754 --> 00:53:40,133
I should have taken care of you
a bit longer back then.

674
00:53:41,259 --> 00:53:43,136
If I did, you wouldn't have suffered
for so long.

675
00:53:51,436 --> 00:53:52,771
I'm sorry.

676
00:53:56,608 --> 00:53:57,734
Mother.

677
00:53:59,235 --> 00:54:02,280
In Korea, I heard you call
your boyfriend and girlfriend's parents

678
00:54:03,031 --> 00:54:05,700
Mother and Father. Am I right?

679
00:54:07,035 --> 00:54:10,080
I've found many mothers in Korea.

680
00:54:11,581 --> 00:54:13,041
I found my real mother

681
00:54:14,334 --> 00:54:16,503
and I can even call you Mother.

682
00:54:18,129 --> 00:54:19,673
I don't deserve

683
00:54:20,131 --> 00:54:23,093
to be called as a mother by you.

684
00:54:23,927 --> 00:54:27,180
I know it's too late to ask
for forgiveness,

685
00:54:29,391 --> 00:54:30,600
but I'm sorry.

686
00:54:31,893 --> 00:54:33,812
If it weren't for you back then,

687
00:54:35,897 --> 00:54:38,858
I would've really been a child abandoned
in a strange neighborhood.

688
00:54:39,526 --> 00:54:40,568
But you took

689
00:54:40,986 --> 00:54:43,947
a strange kid home
and even fed him dinner.

690
00:54:44,948 --> 00:54:46,324
You took care of him.

691
00:54:52,288 --> 00:54:53,415
Thank you.

692
00:55:02,841 --> 00:55:04,592
I know it's too late,

693
00:55:05,385 --> 00:55:07,220
but thank you for taking care of me

694
00:55:07,929 --> 00:55:09,764
and loving me.

695
00:55:12,517 --> 00:55:14,144
I'm really grateful, Mother.

696
00:55:36,958 --> 00:55:38,084
I've decided

697
00:55:39,002 --> 00:55:40,378
to go visit Duk-su

698
00:55:40,462 --> 00:55:42,172
with my mom.

699
00:55:43,965 --> 00:55:45,008
She said

700
00:55:45,759 --> 00:55:47,135
she went every year without me knowing.

701
00:55:50,263 --> 00:55:51,306
Also,

702
00:55:52,807 --> 00:55:55,810
I'll be sorry that my mom sent you
to the orphanage

703
00:55:57,562 --> 00:55:59,189
for the rest of my life.

704
00:56:08,698 --> 00:56:09,866
Duk-mi.

705
00:56:11,951 --> 00:56:13,161
That memory

706
00:56:16,498 --> 00:56:19,084
is a hurtful past
for the seven-year-old Yun-jae,

707
00:56:20,210 --> 00:56:22,087
but it's nothing to me now.

708
00:56:23,463 --> 00:56:24,589
So,

709
00:56:27,217 --> 00:56:29,594
you don't have to be sorry any longer.

710
00:56:30,845 --> 00:56:31,846
Okay?

711
00:56:35,183 --> 00:56:36,559
Good memories

712
00:56:38,353 --> 00:56:39,646
and precious memories.

713
00:56:43,191 --> 00:56:44,651
Give them to me from now on.

714
00:56:45,568 --> 00:56:46,861
Many of them.

715
00:56:51,449 --> 00:56:52,450
I will

716
00:56:53,952 --> 00:56:55,703
love you even more.

717
00:56:57,413 --> 00:56:59,707
So you will become happy now.

718
00:57:02,335 --> 00:57:04,170
I'm already receiving enough love.

719
00:57:11,970 --> 00:57:13,680
And take me with you

720
00:57:15,056 --> 00:57:16,307
to see Duk-su.

721
00:57:31,656 --> 00:57:35,577
Okay. Good, hold him tight.

722
00:57:35,660 --> 00:57:38,079
CHOIKANG JUDO

723
00:57:39,956 --> 00:57:41,499
Watch it.

724
00:57:49,007 --> 00:57:50,091
Go!

725
00:57:54,762 --> 00:57:56,097
Mister, when does your class end?

726
00:57:56,389 --> 00:57:57,474
Why are you asking that?

727
00:57:57,557 --> 00:57:59,601
If you're finished with your class,
give me a ride home.

728
00:57:59,684 --> 00:58:01,227
You'll go there anyway.

729
00:58:04,063 --> 00:58:07,400
I have a question for you.
Do you think I'm a pushover?

730
00:58:08,401 --> 00:58:09,402
A little bit.

731
00:58:09,777 --> 00:58:11,863
Class is not over yet,
so take the bus home.

732
00:58:16,659 --> 00:58:17,785
By the way, mister.

733
00:58:19,037 --> 00:58:20,413
Stop calling me that.

734
00:58:20,497 --> 00:58:24,792
Can I get a discount here
since we know each other?

735
00:58:27,212 --> 00:58:28,588
Of course you can, ma'am.

736
00:58:29,672 --> 00:58:31,883
You can receive
a special ten percent discount

737
00:58:32,133 --> 00:58:34,552
and an additional ten percent
if you bring a friend with you.

738
00:58:34,677 --> 00:58:36,054
Would you like to register?

739
00:58:36,638 --> 00:58:37,680
No.

740
00:58:40,141 --> 00:58:43,019
Come back here. Hey. You!

741
00:58:43,561 --> 00:58:45,146
COMMUNITY SERVICE CENTER

742
00:58:47,649 --> 00:58:49,484
I love everything that you cook, Mom.

743
00:58:54,948 --> 00:58:57,408
How could she call her, Mom? Why?

744
00:59:01,120 --> 00:59:02,956
Ma'am, here is
your Family Relation Certificate.

745
00:59:04,457 --> 00:59:05,792
FAMILY RELATION CERTIFICATE

746
00:59:08,795 --> 00:59:10,171
She didn't take her name out of it yet.

747
00:59:10,547 --> 00:59:12,006
-Let's go.
-Where to?

748
00:59:12,715 --> 00:59:14,425
To find my daughter.

749
00:59:16,010 --> 00:59:16,844
Okay.

750
00:59:25,603 --> 00:59:27,313
What did Director Gold say?

751
00:59:29,732 --> 00:59:33,111
He said it was okay,
and even comforted me.

752
00:59:34,862 --> 00:59:37,282
I felt so sorry and thankful
at the same time.

753
00:59:45,290 --> 00:59:46,332
Mom?

754
00:59:47,959 --> 00:59:49,627
How did you know I was here?

755
00:59:51,671 --> 00:59:53,006
Did you tail me?

756
00:59:53,673 --> 00:59:56,509
You're the one who kicked me out.
Why are you here?

757
00:59:57,427 --> 00:59:58,511
Hyo-jin.

758
00:59:58,595 --> 01:00:01,055
First, let's go home and talk.

759
01:00:01,639 --> 01:00:02,724
Let's go.

760
01:00:05,226 --> 01:00:07,312
This is my home now!

761
01:00:09,272 --> 01:00:10,523
What do you think about this?

762
01:00:10,690 --> 01:00:11,941
-Well...
-Catch her.

763
01:00:12,317 --> 01:00:14,360
-Let's go. Come!
-Let me go!

764
01:00:14,444 --> 01:00:15,903
-I don't want to go!
-Hey!

765
01:00:15,987 --> 01:00:17,822
Let me go!

766
01:00:18,406 --> 01:00:20,283
I'm so glad that he was able
to meet great parents.

767
01:00:20,366 --> 01:00:23,036
-Come over here!
-I don't want to go!

768
01:00:23,119 --> 01:00:24,662
-What's that sound?
-What's that sound?

769
01:00:24,746 --> 01:00:26,623
I don't want to go! Let me go!

770
01:00:26,706 --> 01:00:28,499
-Mom!
-Open the door!

771
01:00:28,583 --> 01:00:30,418
-I don't want to go!
-Who are you?

772
01:00:30,501 --> 01:00:31,669
-Who are you?
-My goodness.

773
01:00:31,753 --> 01:00:33,588
What do you think you're doing?

774
01:00:33,671 --> 01:00:35,965
Who are you? Why are you trying
to take my daughter?

775
01:00:36,299 --> 01:00:38,551
Hyo-jin is my daughter!

776
01:00:38,968 --> 01:00:41,429
Why do you keep saying
she's your daughter when she's mine?

777
01:00:41,512 --> 01:00:43,389
She's my daughter! Move!

778
01:00:43,681 --> 01:00:45,350
Mr. Kim, tell them to get out of our way!

779
01:00:45,433 --> 01:00:46,684
-Excuse me.
-Move!

780
01:00:46,768 --> 01:00:50,438
Hyo-jin is my daughter! Hey, Hyo-jin!
Are you or are you not my daughter?

781
01:00:50,563 --> 01:00:51,439
You're my daughter!

782
01:00:52,732 --> 01:00:54,233
Mr. Kim, what do you think about this?

783
01:00:55,026 --> 01:00:56,110
Move!

784
01:01:05,328 --> 01:01:08,206
I'm sorry. I didn't know
you were Hyo-jin's mother.

785
01:01:08,706 --> 01:01:10,166
How could you not know?

786
01:01:10,541 --> 01:01:12,585
We look exactly the same.

787
01:01:18,508 --> 01:01:21,969
Hyo-jin, pack your stuff
and go home with your mom.

788
01:01:22,387 --> 01:01:23,304
Mom.

789
01:01:24,305 --> 01:01:26,224
Why do you keep calling her that?

790
01:01:27,684 --> 01:01:30,687
It was wrong of her
to pack your stuff and kick you out.

791
01:01:30,937 --> 01:01:35,024
But now that she's here for you,
it's only right that you go back.

792
01:01:39,779 --> 01:01:41,239
And as for Hyo-jin's mother...

793
01:01:41,322 --> 01:01:43,533
My name is Eom So-hye.

794
01:01:43,616 --> 01:01:44,867
Hyo-jin's mother.

795
01:01:45,910 --> 01:01:48,663
I heard there are people
who don't like being referred

796
01:01:48,746 --> 01:01:50,873
to as somebody's mother.

797
01:01:51,207 --> 01:01:54,377
But maybe it's because
I'm old-fashioned, I like it.

798
01:01:54,460 --> 01:01:56,963
I like it when people call me
Duk-mi's mother.

799
01:01:58,089 --> 01:02:00,091
It feels as if the entire world
is acknowledging the fact

800
01:02:00,174 --> 01:02:02,885
that I'm the mother of my precious child.

801
01:02:04,554 --> 01:02:07,724
But you have to know
that it doesn't last that long.

802
01:02:08,558 --> 01:02:10,768
She may be your precious daughter
whom you gave birth to,

803
01:02:10,977 --> 01:02:12,812
but that only lasts
while she lives with you.

804
01:02:14,313 --> 01:02:16,858
You should be nice to her
while she's by your side.

805
01:02:16,941 --> 01:02:19,444
It's why they say "You never miss
the water until the well runs dry."

806
01:02:20,862 --> 01:02:23,656
Doesn't that proverb apply to our kids?

807
01:02:23,865 --> 01:02:26,242
It means they should be good
to their parents while they're alive.

808
01:02:26,325 --> 01:02:27,410
That goes for both ways.

809
01:02:27,785 --> 01:02:30,288
You need to be good to each other
while you're together.

810
01:02:31,372 --> 01:02:33,541
If you end up falling apart
from each other,

811
01:02:33,624 --> 01:02:35,668
that'll be the end
regardless of how much you regret it.

812
01:02:37,712 --> 01:02:39,839
You can't boss your kid around

813
01:02:39,922 --> 01:02:42,508
and mistreat your family.

814
01:02:42,800 --> 01:02:46,137
Married couples,
parents and children, and siblings.

815
01:02:47,013 --> 01:02:48,848
They're all relationships
based on human connection.

816
01:02:48,931 --> 01:02:51,517
So there's not a single relationship
you should take for granted.

817
01:02:52,810 --> 01:02:55,772
But the fact
that you're still making an effort,

818
01:02:55,855 --> 01:02:58,816
although it might be a bit clumsy,
means that you're okay.

819
01:03:00,359 --> 01:03:01,360
Okay?

820
01:03:04,322 --> 01:03:05,531
Okay?

821
01:03:05,698 --> 01:03:08,951
You really have a way with words.

822
01:03:10,828 --> 01:03:11,829
Hyo-jin.

823
01:03:12,580 --> 01:03:14,123
Are you going to come back home now?

824
01:03:15,666 --> 01:03:16,751
Yes, I will.

825
01:03:17,043 --> 01:03:18,669
She says she's going to come back home.

826
01:03:19,712 --> 01:03:22,006
She's my daughter. Don't we look alike?

827
01:03:23,925 --> 01:03:25,676
She's pretty because she takes after me.

828
01:03:29,972 --> 01:03:31,682
-Thank you.
-No problem.

829
01:03:32,433 --> 01:03:34,018
I'll visit again.

830
01:03:35,853 --> 01:03:37,396
You're welcome anytime.

831
01:03:37,897 --> 01:03:39,774
Just don't come here
after you fight with your mom.

832
01:03:45,655 --> 01:03:46,781
Bye.

833
01:04:01,295 --> 01:04:02,547
This is a problem.

834
01:04:02,755 --> 01:04:04,715
What's wrong? Don't you like it?

835
01:04:05,508 --> 01:04:06,759
It's too good.

836
01:04:07,677 --> 01:04:10,179
You startled me a little
because there's no way it'd be bad.

837
01:04:10,972 --> 01:04:12,056
Ms. Choi.

838
01:04:12,557 --> 01:04:15,059
Let's also work together
on my next album. Deal?

839
01:04:16,352 --> 01:04:18,688
I'll think about it.

840
01:04:19,689 --> 01:04:21,315
I'm really looking forward
to the exhibition.

841
01:04:23,901 --> 01:04:26,445
How about we use this color

842
01:04:26,904 --> 01:04:27,947
to highlight the main wall?

843
01:04:28,030 --> 01:04:30,408
I looked into it
because I also liked this color.

844
01:04:30,491 --> 01:04:33,035
But I heard it's going to be hard
to mix the right colors.

845
01:04:33,119 --> 01:04:35,496
-Let's go see when they paint it.
-Okay.

846
01:04:35,663 --> 01:04:36,747
Who are we, everyone?

847
01:04:36,831 --> 01:04:38,332
-The museum guards!
-The museum guards!

848
01:04:38,416 --> 01:04:41,669
-Right. Here are your basic tasks.
-Number one.

849
01:04:41,752 --> 01:04:43,546
Please be careful when you move it.

850
01:04:43,629 --> 01:04:44,839
-Okay.
-Okay.

851
01:04:58,561 --> 01:05:00,062
You must all be exhausted.

852
01:05:00,479 --> 01:05:01,939
Here. Cheer up.

853
01:05:03,816 --> 01:05:05,860
-Here you go, Ms. Yu.
-Thank you.

854
01:05:07,403 --> 01:05:09,238
I'm sorry. This is for women.

855
01:05:14,160 --> 01:05:16,579
There's not much time left,
so let's really put in our all.

856
01:05:23,669 --> 01:05:24,921
Aren't you tired?

857
01:05:26,380 --> 01:05:27,340
A little.

858
01:05:27,715 --> 01:05:28,799
But I'm having fun.

859
01:05:29,050 --> 01:05:32,011
I'll finally get to see the exhibition
that we've been planning for so long.

860
01:05:32,094 --> 01:05:33,930
Let's keep the spirit for a little longer.

861
01:05:34,013 --> 01:05:36,682
Okay, I'll do that, Ms. Sung.

862
01:05:38,601 --> 01:05:39,894
Should we go to my place?

863
01:05:40,645 --> 01:05:42,188
I'll go if you buy me something delicious.

864
01:05:42,438 --> 01:05:44,440
There's something even better than that.

865
01:05:44,774 --> 01:05:45,900
What's that?

866
01:05:46,359 --> 01:05:49,070
Your birthday gift is at my place.

867
01:05:49,862 --> 01:05:51,155
Would you like to take it?

868
01:05:59,538 --> 01:06:00,706
Where is it?

869
01:06:03,960 --> 01:06:05,044
Close your eyes.

870
01:06:06,629 --> 01:06:08,130
You're trying to pull a prank, aren't you?

871
01:06:08,214 --> 01:06:09,799
Can I just have it?

872
01:06:10,216 --> 01:06:13,469
I listened to you when you asked me
to close my eyes.

873
01:06:14,303 --> 01:06:15,596
Don't you trust me?

874
01:06:16,389 --> 01:06:17,932
That's how you're going to play it?

875
01:06:18,933 --> 01:06:20,768
Okay, I'll keep my eyes closed.

876
01:06:21,686 --> 01:06:23,270
-Follow me.
-Okay.

877
01:06:32,530 --> 01:06:34,532
You don't know
how much I'm looking forward to this.

878
01:06:35,700 --> 01:06:37,326
Don't get too excited though.

879
01:06:40,913 --> 01:06:42,832
-Are you ready?
-Yes.

880
01:07:15,114 --> 01:07:16,157
Director Gold.

881
01:07:17,366 --> 01:07:18,367
I'm...

882
01:07:21,495 --> 01:07:23,456
finally able to paint again.

883
01:07:26,751 --> 01:07:29,045
-I'm a bit rusty, so--
-It's perfect.

884
01:07:33,758 --> 01:07:35,509
I'll practice more.

885
01:07:35,593 --> 01:07:37,136
It's already perfect.

886
01:07:43,184 --> 01:07:44,310
It's perfect.

887
01:08:14,590 --> 01:08:16,759
You also held my hand like this

888
01:08:18,469 --> 01:08:21,055
when we first met.

889
01:08:21,555 --> 01:08:22,473
Do you remember?

890
01:08:25,768 --> 01:08:26,894
"Hello."

891
01:08:27,436 --> 01:08:29,522
My name is Sung Duk-mi.

892
01:08:34,110 --> 01:08:35,653
What's your name?

893
01:08:36,362 --> 01:08:37,530
That's what you said.

894
01:08:40,783 --> 01:08:42,243
Do you remember what I said?

895
01:08:42,827 --> 01:08:44,161
My name is

896
01:08:46,122 --> 01:08:47,289
Heo Yun-jae.

897
01:08:48,999 --> 01:08:50,376
"Heo Yun-jae."

898
01:09:00,386 --> 01:09:02,304
Now that I think about it,

899
01:09:04,682 --> 01:09:07,560
the reason I wasn't able to paint
when that was all that I had

900
01:09:10,604 --> 01:09:12,148
was probably
because the universe wanted me

901
01:09:12,231 --> 01:09:13,732
to find something even more precious.

902
01:09:17,778 --> 01:09:19,405
And that's exactly what you are to me.

903
01:09:51,604 --> 01:09:52,938
It took too long

904
01:09:53,731 --> 01:09:55,107
to finally meet you again.

905
01:09:58,402 --> 01:10:00,404
I missed you, Duk-mi.

906
01:10:02,364 --> 01:10:04,909
I missed you, Yun-jae.

907
01:10:10,623 --> 01:10:11,832
Hi, Duk-mi.

908
01:10:15,002 --> 01:10:16,420
Hi, Yun-jae.

909
01:10:57,419 --> 01:10:59,630
Didn't you say you had
something important at 5 p.m.?

910
01:10:59,797 --> 01:11:00,923
Should we do it together?

911
01:11:01,590 --> 01:11:03,342
My boyfriend has
the hands of the Almighty!

912
01:11:03,425 --> 01:11:04,385
You're so adorable.

913
01:11:04,468 --> 01:11:06,553
A railroad and The Road to Si-an.

914
01:11:06,720 --> 01:11:08,347
Now, call me The Road to Ryan.

915
01:11:08,430 --> 01:11:10,557
Does that mean Ms. Sung needs
to go to the States?

916
01:11:10,641 --> 01:11:12,434
There's no way she'd leave
without Director Gold.

917
01:11:12,518 --> 01:11:13,686
You don't think she'll go, right?

918
01:11:13,769 --> 01:11:14,979
Take care, all right?

919
01:11:15,104 --> 01:11:17,273
You're finally going.

920
01:11:17,690 --> 01:11:19,108
Did you have sweet dreams?

921
01:11:19,650 --> 01:11:21,318
They were sweet
because they were my memories.

922
01:11:21,610 --> 01:11:23,696
However, they were a bit sad too.

923
01:11:24,071 --> 01:11:26,448
Subtitle translation by Seul-ki Kim

